/title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WeTheChangePodcast/~3/hkzzEFmsdxE/</link><category>Podcast</category><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">todd.goldfarb@gmail.com (Todd Goldfarb)</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 06 Feb 2008 07:39:21 PST</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.wethechange.com/podcast-launch-conversations-to-change-the-world/</guid><content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<p><img align="right" src="http://www.wethechange.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/02/conversations100pixwide.jpg" alt="conversations100pixwide.jpg" title="conversations100pixwide.jpg" />I am excited. Today is the launch of We The Change&#8217;s podcast, which I am calling &#8220;Conversations to Change The World&#8221;!</p>
<p><strong>Each Wednesday</strong> I will interview one expert from somewhere across the mind-body-spirit continuum and pick their brain. The goal is pretty straight-forward: to spread greater awareness of all the fantastic people and organizations which are doing meaningful work to improve people&#8217;s lives and make the word a better place!</p>
<p>Today I have with me Guy Finley, best-selling author of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.beunstoppable.org/?refsrc=CD818">The Secret of Letting Go</a> and more than 30 other books and audio albums that have sold over a million copies in 16 languages worldwide.</p>
<p>I loved speaking with Guy because he has a flair for entertainment (his father was Larry Finley, late night TV pioneer) and his message is clear and concise. In today&#8217;s show, Guy provides us with two prime elements for maintaining long-term happiness&#8230;here is the link to the pod:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.wethechange.com/podcast/GuyFinley.mp3"><strong>Guy Finley Interview</strong></a></p>
<p><img align="left" width="79" src="http://www.wethechange.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/02/guy-redshirt-icon.thumbnail.jpg" alt="guy-redshirt-icon.jpg" height="95" style="width: 79px; height: 95px" title="guy-redshirt-icon.jpg" />Guy has been a guest on over 400 television and radio shows, including national appearances on ABC, NBC, CBS, CNN, NPR, Wisdom Network, and many others&#8230;so its a real pleasure to have him here.</p>
<p><strong>   </strong></p>
<p><strong>Why a Podcast!</strong></p>
<p>The spark for creating this podcast came to me upon the following realization: I am only one guy! Because my intention for this website is to be a platform for change, it makes a whole lot of sense to enlist the knowledge of outside experts.</p>
<p>My goal is to have the podcasts serve as a learning experience for all the readers of this blog. My ultimate objective is the following:</p>
<p><em>To become the Larry King of the blogosphere, where only positive improvement methods are explored.</em></p>
<p>I simply have no interest in interviewing people unless they are involved with bringing sustainable and helpful solutions into the world. AND, isn&#8217;t it time to have a &#8220;talk show&#8221; that <em>only</em> discusses all of the positive things going on all over the globe?</p>
<p><strong>Next Week&#8217;s Show</strong></p>
<p>Next Wednesday we have a real treat. I will interview Jeff McIntire-Strasburg, Senior Editor and Content Director at Green Options. He&#8217;s also the writer/publisher of <a href="http://sustainablog.org/"><font color="#137a98">sustainablog</font></a>, and a former writer at <a href="http://www.treehugger.com/"><font color="#137a98">Treehugger</font></a>.</p>
<p>You may be shocked, and excited, to hear some of the environmentally sound products currently being developed (someone say electric cars&#8230;)?</p>
<p>Starting next week these pods will be available on i-tunes, where you will be able to subscribe to the show download episodes onto your i-pod. Since this is my first pod, I have to wait for i-tunes to approve the podcast.</p>
<p>Again, here is the link to my interview with Guy Finley&#8230;Enjoy!</p>
